# Area Tecnica (Sector Pro) — Cursor Rules

## Stack & Platform
React 18 + TypeScript + Vite 6 + Supabase + Tailwind + shadcn/ui + TanStack Query + Zustand.
Deploy: `dev` preview, `main` production (`sector-pro.work`).

## Mandatory Rules
- Work on `dev` branch by default; never commit directly to `main`.
- Always install deps with: `npm install --legacy-peer-deps`.
- Never add `package-lock.json`.
- Keep `date-fns` at `^3.6.0` unless explicitly migrating.
- Do not add `lovable-tagger`.
- Maintain Supabase schema/RLS compatibility.

## Architecture Conventions
- Follow domain-based structure in `src/components/*` and `src/features/*`.
- Keep route-level code in `src/pages/*` (lazy-loading preserved).
- Prefer shared logic in `src/hooks/*`, `src/lib/*`, and `src/utils/*`.
- Use existing Zustand stores in `src/stores/*` for global state.
- Reuse query patterns from TanStack Query setup instead of ad-hoc data loading.
- Use `@/` imports.

## Key Code Areas
- UI domains: festival, tours, jobs, matrix, equipment, logistics, messages, timesheet, lights, sound, video.
- Backend: `supabase/migrations/*` and `supabase/functions/*`.
- Integrations/types: `src/integrations/supabase/{client.ts,types.ts}`.

## Validation (run as relevant)
- `npm run lint`
- `npm run test:run`
- `npm run build`
- `npm run lint:functions` (if Edge Functions touched)
- `npm run cap:sync` (if mobile runtime affected)
